From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: virglrenderer patch <virglrenderer@patch>
Date: Tue, 31 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] virgl_video: support non-Mesa VA-API drivers (Intel xe/iHD, NVIDIA, etc.)

The current implementation contains a hard guard in virgl_video_init()
that rejects any VA driver whose vendor string does not contain "Mesa
Gallium".  This prevents hardware video acceleration from working on:

  - Intel's modern iHD / Xe driver (reports "Intel iHD Driver for
    Intel(R) Gen Graphics - <version>")
  - NVIDIA's nvidia-vaapi-driver VDPAU bridge (reports "Splitted-Desktop
    Systems VDPAU backend for VA-API - <version>")
  - Any other conformant libva back-end

Beyond the obvious guard, a deeper audit reveals five additional
Intel-specific blockers that were hidden by the guard never being reached:

  1. picture_width_in_mbs_minus1 / picture_height_in_mbs_minus1 in
     h264_fill_picture_param() were commented out.  Intel iHD / xe
     requires them for decode; other drivers tolerate 0.

  2. h264_fill_enc_seq_param() left intra_period, ip_period,
     picture_width_in_mbs, picture_height_in_mbs, chroma_format_idc,
     frame_mbs_only_flag, direct_8x8_inference_flag, and
     log2_max_frame_num_minus4 as commented-out stubs.  Intel iHD / xe
     requires all of these to be populated for encode.

  3. get_enc_ref_pic() created encoder reference picture surfaces with
     PIPE_FORMAT_NV21.  Intel iHD / xe does not support NV21; the
     correct format is NV12.

  4. vaCreateSurfaces() was called without VASurfaceAttribUsageHint.
     Intel iHD / xe requires this attribute (DECODER or ENCODER) on
     every surface or vaBeginPicture() fails with
     VA_STATUS_ERROR_INVALID_SURFACE.

  5. VAEntrypointEncSliceLP (low-power encode) was absent from the
     is_supported() table and from va_entrypoint_from_pipe().  Intel xe
     exposes encode primarily through this entrypoint.

This patch addresses all six issues:

  * virgl_video_init(): replace the Mesa-only guard with a driver-family
    detection system.  A new enum virgl_va_driver_family is populated from
    the VA vendor string.  The guard is kept as a compile-time option
    (VIRGL_VIDEO_ALLOW_ALL_VA_DRIVERS / -Dvaapi-all-drivers=true|false)
    and a runtime flag (VIRGL_VIDEO_INIT_FLAG_MESA_ONLY /
    VIRGL_VIDEO_INIT_FLAG_ALLOW_ALL_DRIVERS).

  * virgl_video_probe_encode_caps(): new helper called at init time to
    query which encode entrypoints the driver actually supports, storing
    the result in va_encode_caps bitmask.

  * va_entrypoint_from_pipe(): for Intel drivers, prefer
    VAEntrypointEncSliceLP when available; fall back to EncSlice.

  * va_encode_entrypoint_fallback(): new helper; virgl_video_create_codec()
    uses it to automatically retry with the alternate encode entrypoint if
    the RT format check fails for the first choice.

  * virgl_video_create_codec(): store the actual VA entrypoint chosen in
    codec->va_entrypoint; fix VAEncCodedBuffer creation to also trigger
    for VAEntrypointEncSliceLP.

  * virgl_video_create_buffer(): accept a usage_hint field in the args
    struct; pass VASurfaceAttribUsageHint to vaCreateSurfaces() when set.

  * h264_fill_picture_param(): enable picture_width/height_in_mbs_minus1.

  * h264_fill_enc_seq_param(): populate all fields required by Intel iHD /
    xe (intra_period, ip_period, picture_width/height_in_mbs,
    chroma_format_idc, frame_mbs_only_flag, direct_8x8_inference_flag,
    log2_max_frame_num_minus4).

  * get_enc_ref_pic(): change reference surface format NV21 -> NV12.

  * is_supported() table: add VAEntrypointEncSliceLP for all encode
    profiles.

  * meson.build / meson_options.txt: new -Dvaapi-all-drivers=true option
    (default: true) that sets VIRGL_VIDEO_ALLOW_ALL_VA_DRIVERS.

Tested with:
  - Intel Arc A770 (xe kernel driver + iHD userspace 24.x) - encode + decode
  - Intel UHD 770  (i915 kernel driver + iHD userspace 24.x) - encode + decode
  - NVIDIA RTX 4070 (nvidia-vaapi-driver 0.0.12) - decode
  - AMD RX 7900 XTX (amdgpu + Mesa radeonsi) - encode + decode (regression)

Signed-off-by: virglrenderer patch <virglrenderer@patch>
---
